5 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 1210.508F,
6 as last amended by Section 3, Chapter 297, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S.
7 Supp. 2025, Section 1210.508F), is amended to read as follows:
8 Section 1210.508F. A. The Commission for Educational Quality
9 and Accountability shall ensure that the reading competencies for
10 elementary teachers are included in the competencies for special
11 education teachers.
12 B. The Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability in
13 collaboration with the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education
14 shall ensure that all teachers and adjuncts of early childhood
15 education, elementary education, and special education are provided
16 quality training in intervention, instruction, and remediation
17 strategies in the science of reading to provide explicit and
18 systematic instruction in phonological awareness, decoding, fluency,
19 vocabulary, and comprehension and implement reading strategies that
20 research has shown to be successful in improving reading among
21 students with reading difficulties. In addition, quality education
22 for prospective teachers shall be provided in research-based
23 instructional strategies for instruction, assessment, and
24 intervention for literacy development for all students including
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1778 SFLR Page 19
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 adva nced readers, typically developing readers, and struggling
2 readers who are coping with a range of challenges including, but not
3 limited to, English learners and learners with handicapping
4 conditions and learning disabilities, including dyslexia. Quality
5 training shall include guidance from professional resources such as
6 the Report of the National Reading Panel, Response to Intervention
7 guidelines, and professional organizations such as the Council for
8 Exceptional Children, International Dyslexia Association,
9 International Literacy Association, National Council of Teachers of
10 English, and National Association for the Education of Young
11 Children.
12 C. All institutions within The Oklahoma State System of Higher
13 Education that offer elementary, early childhood education, or
14 special education programs approved by the Commission for
15 Educational Quality and Accountability shall incorporate into those
16 programs the requirement that teacher candidates study the five
17 elements of reading instruction, which are phonological awareness,
18 decoding, fluency, vocabulary, and comprehension. Teacher
19 candidates shall study strategies including, but not limited to,
20 instruction that is explicitly taught, sequenced, multimodal
21 (reading, writing, speaking, listening, hands-on, etc.),
22 multidisciplinary, and reflective to adapt for individual learners.
23 D. Each teacher education program approved by the Commission
24 for Educational Quality and Accountability shall be audited by the
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1778 SFLR Page 20
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Comm ission to ensure teacher candidates are receiving quality
2 training in the science of reading in compliance with the provisions
3 of subsections B and C of this section. The Commission shall place
4 the accreditation of any noncompliant teacher education program on
5 probationary status and provide guidance for exiting probationary
6 status.
7 E. Effective July 1, 2025, any person seeking initial
8 certification in a special education, early childhood education, or
9 elementary education program in this state shall be required to
10 successfully complete a comprehensive reading instruction assessment
11 approved by the Commission for Educational Quality and
12 Accountability as a condition for certification. The assessment
13 shall evaluate the certification applicant’s knowledge and
14 understanding of the five elements of reading instruction, which are
15 phonological awareness, decoding, fluency, vocabulary, and
16 comprehension.
17 E. F. Candidates applying for adjunct positions, an alternative
18 placement teaching certificate, or an emergency teaching certificate
19 in elementary education shall complete instruction in the science of
20 reading as determined by the Commission for Educational Quality and
21 Accountability and the State Board of Education.
22 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
23 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1778 SFLR Page 21
